  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Amana, Whirlpool family value tier since 2001</h2>
    <p>Whirlpool Corporation acquired Amana in 2001 from Goodman Global. Since then, Amana has operated as the value tier within Whirlpool's North American brand family, positioned below Whirlpool mainstream + Maytag mass-market and above Roper entry-tier. The shared Whirlpool Corporation parent gives Amana a distinctive service advantage over independent value-tier brands: parts commonality with Whirlpool mainstream + Maytag comparable models at the mid-tier chassis level, which translates to strong parts supply through Whirlpool Corporation's North American distribution (one of the largest appliance-parts networks in the US).</p>
    <p>For LA service economics, this converts Amana from a value-tier budget brand with uncertain service outlook into a value-tier budget brand backed by one of the strongest parts-supply chains in the appliance-repair market. Common Amana wall oven parts 1-3 day lead through Whirlpool distribution; specialty components 3-5 days.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Amana wall oven models we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Amana 30" single built-in wall oven</h3><p>Value-tier single-cavity. Practical bake + broil + self-clean. Service: bake/broil element, control board, sensors, door hardware.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Amana 30" double built-in wall oven</h3><p>Stacked dual-cavity. Upper + lower independent elements + sensors, shared primary control.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Whirlpool family parts commonality</h3><p>Bake/broil elements, convection fan motors, many sensor + control variants interchange with Whirlpool mainstream + Maytag siblings at comparable spec level.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Convection on higher-spec Amana</h3><p>Not all Amana wall ovens include convection. When present, service pattern standard: convection fan + element where applicable.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Self-clean pyrolytic cycle</h3><p>Standard self-clean on Amana wall oven models that include the feature. Door-lock motor + thermal sensor service.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Whirlpool distribution advantage</h3><p>Parts availability through one of the largest US appliance-parts networks, genuine service-economics advantage over independent value-tier brands.</p></div>
    </div>
